# Request Validation — Fastify Schema

## Rule

Every `POST`/`PUT`/`PATCH` route **must** declare `schema: { body: ... }` in its route options.  
Controllers **must not** contain manual presence or type guards.

## Route (define the schema here)

```typescript
// apps/server/src/api/routes/mcp.route.ts
const myToolBodySchema = {
  type: "object",
  required: ["title", "fix"],
  properties: {
    title:    { type: "string", minLength: 1 },
    fix:      { type: "string", minLength: 1 },
    severity: { type: "string", enum: ["critical", "high", "medium", "low"], default: "medium" },
    tags:     { type: "array", items: { type: "string" }, default: [] },
  },
};

app.post("/tools/my_tool", {
  preHandler: [requireProjectAuth],
  schema: { body: myToolBodySchema },   // ← required
}, withMcpRouteLogging("my_tool", handler));
```

## Controller (trust the validated body)

```typescript
// apps/server/src/api/controllers/my-tool.controller.ts
export const myToolHandler = async (request: FastifyRequest, reply: FastifyReply) => {
  const { title, fix, severity, tags } = request.body as MyToolBody; // already validated + defaults applied
  // call service directly — no guards needed
};
```

## What Fastify does automatically

| Scenario | Behaviour |
|---|---|
| Required field missing | `400 { error: "validation_error" }` (before auth runs) |
| Wrong type | `400 { error: "validation_error" }` |
| Invalid enum value | `400 { error: "validation_error" }` |
| Field with `default:` absent | Ajv injects the default — controller always sees a value |

The `setErrorHandler` in `apps/server/src/api/app.ts` maps Fastify's `FST_ERR_VALIDATION` errors to `{ error: "validation_error" }` to match the rest of the API's error shape.
